## Step 20: Emit phase_completed event

Log the ship run as an event so `/palantir-mini:pm-retro` and BackwardProp can track shipping velocity, coverage trends, and plan completion across time.

Call `mcp__palantir-mini__emit_event` with:

```json
{
  "type": "phase_completed",
  "skill": "pm-ship",
  "phase": "ship",
  "branch": "<current-branch>",
  "base": "<base>",
  "version": "<NEW_VERSION or CURRENT_VERSION>",
  "commit": "<git rev-parse --short HEAD>",
  "pr_url": "<PR URL>",
  "metrics": {
    "coverage_pct": N,
    "plan_items_total": N,
    "plan_items_done": N,
    "review_findings": N,
    "review_auto_fixed": N,
    "review_asked": N
  },
  "preflight": {
    "schema_pin": "pass | blocked",
    "doc_drift": "clean | findings",
    "team_health": "green | yellow | red | n/a"
  }
}
```

The event carries the 5 Decision Lineage dimensions automatically (`when`, `atopWhich` = commit SHA, `throughWhich` = `pm-ship`, `byWhom` = identity + agent, `withWhat` = reasoning + hypothesis) per `~/.claude/rules/10-events-jsonl.md`. Never rewrite or truncate `events.jsonl`.

This step is automatic — never skip it, never ask for confirmation.

